section.div:
✨ **
feat(workflows)**: Add workflow telemetry for better monitoring
This commit adds the workflow telemetry feature to the GitHub workflows. The `catchpoint/workflow-telemetry-action` v1.8.7 action is used to integrate telemetry functionality. The action is configured to enable system process tracing, dark theme, and commenting on pull requests. This addition will provide better insights and monitoring for the workflows.
✨ **
feat(workflows)**: Resolve component packages from bit.cloud registry
This commit introduces a step in the workflows to resolve component packages from the bit.cloud registry. The step configures npm to use the bit.cloud registry and sets the authentication token. This change is necessary for component installation using package managers other than Bit.
💄 **
style(workflows)**: Remove unnecessary conditional check in CLA Assistant
This commit removes an unnecessary conditional check in the CLA workflow. The conditional check on the `cla_enabled` environment variable is removed, as it is redundant and does not affect the workflow's functionality.
♻️ **
refactor(workflows)**: Cleanup and standardize workflow files
This commit standardizes and cleans up various workflow files. The changes ensure consistency and improve readability across the workflow files. No functional changes are included in this commit.
🔨 **
fix(workflows)**: Update file modification date in GitHub Management workflow
This commit updates the last modified date in the header comment of the GitHub Management workflow file. The modification date is corrected to reflect the actual date of the file modification.
🐛 **
fix(workflows)**: Use correct workflow telemetry action in GitGuardian IAC scan
This commit fixes a mistake in the GitGuardian IAC scan workflow. The workflow telemetry action was using an incorrect version. The action is now correctly set to `catchpoint/workflow-telemetry-action@v1.8.7` for better monitoring and insights.
🎨 **
style(workflows)**: Update header comment in Lane Cleanup workflow
This commit updates the header comment in the Lane Cleanup workflow file to include relevant information. The header comment now includes the project, file path, author information, and license details. The modification date is also updated to reflect the latest changes.
Signed-off-by: Jonathan Stevens <jonathan.stevens@eventiva.co.uk>
